There were quite a few small scale rebellions during the Edo period mostly
during poor harvest periods. I don&#39;t recall what weapons they used.
Shimabara&#39;s revolt involved ronin as well as peasants. Some books that might
help &#39;Peasant protests and uprisings in Tokugawa Japan&#39; Stephan Vlastos,
&#39;Peasant Protest in Japan&#39; Herbert Bix. Both books focus on the social
conditions of the revolts, not on the military aspects.
